<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-06-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-06-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="743" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d743">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861a.01/288</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Japanese Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Saburi</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <p>The Japanese Chargé d’Affaires presents his compliments to the Honorable
                            the Secretary of State and, acting under instructions from the Japanese
                            Government, has the honor to inform him that on the 24th of June the
                            following announcement was made public in Tokio: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“The Japanese Government have decided to withdraw all the
                                    Japanese troops from the Maritime Province of Siberia by the end
                                    of October 1922. Suitable measures will be taken for the
                                    protection of resident Japanese subjects.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer>
                            <dateline rendition="#left">
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-24">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 24, 1922</hi>
                                </date>, <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>.</dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>